  "text": "Feeding experiments. Adult rats were fasted for 48 h and given 5 g of powdered rat chow (Purina), some of which contained 5% (wt/wt) cholestyramine or 2% (wt/wt) TC and 0.5% (wt/wt) sodium cholate. After 4 h, when all food was consumed, rats were anesthetized, hepatic portal blood was collected into EDTA, and plasma was isolated and stored at Ϫ20°C. Plasma was extracted with acid-acetone before RIA for NT using antiserum HC8, which displayed a coefficient of variation of 7.7% [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . To complement this short-term feeding experiment, a second study was performed in which rats were given the same formulated chow (15 g/day) for 5 days. In a third study, fasted rats were given the formulated foods overnight, and tissues were harvested 16 h later for measurement of NT mRNA in 20-cm segments of small intestine. Total RNA was prepared using the guanidinium isothiocyanate extraction method, and NT mRNA was quantitated as described previously (6, [CITATION_3] . Briefly, RNA (20 g) from either the proximal or distal small intestine of individual rats was mixed with rat 32 P-labeled NT and glyceraldehyde-3-phosphate dehydrogenase (GAPDH) antisense probes (3 ϫ 10 5 cpm of each probe), ethanol precipitated, dried, dissolved in 30 l hybridization buffer, and incubated at 42°C for 24 h. The samples were subsequently digested with nucleases P1 (20 g/ml) and T1 (1 g/ml), digested with proteinase K, phenol extracted, ethanol precipitated, dried, and analyzed on sequencing gels. Autoradiographs were scanned and protection products were quantitated using a Bio-Rad Fluor-S MultiImager and MultiAnalyst software. Sense NT mRNA was transcribed from pGEM4-rbNT (2), linearized with BamH I using SP6 RNA polymerase, and analyzed as described above to generate standard curves. Rat 32 P-labeled NT antisense probe was transcribed from EcoR I-linearized prNT4 (2) using T7 RNA polymerase. A rat GAPDH cDNA fragment (nt 882-1016) was amplified by RT-PCR from total rat brain RNA using the following primers: 5Ј-TTTTGAAT-TCAACAGCAACTCCCATTCCT-3Ј and 5Ј-TTTTGGATCCA-TGTAGGCCATGAGGTCCAC-3Ј. The PCR fragment was digested with EcoR I and BamH I and subcloned into pBluescript KS(ϩ) (Stratagene) digested with the same enzymes to create prGAPDH. The plasmid was linearized with EcoR I and transcribed with T7 RNA polymerase to generate 32 Plabeled antisense probe.",
